# .lycheeignore
#
# Regex patterns (one per line) for URLs that lychee should skip.
#
# Rules:
#   1. Add an entry ONLY when a link is verified-good in a browser but
#      consistently fails in CI (e.g. hosts that 999 on HEAD requests,
#      hosts that block GitHub-Actions egress, or rate-limit aggressively).
#   2. Every entry MUST be preceded by a one-line comment explaining
#      WHY it is ignored (host behaviour + date noticed).
#   3. Prefer narrow patterns (specific host) over broad ones.
#   4. Re-evaluate entries during Phase 7.5 review passes.
#
# Examples (commented out, kept for reference):
# # linkedin.com — returns HTTP 999 on HEAD requests from CI runners (2026-04)
# ^https?://(www\.)?linkedin\.com/
# # twitter.com / x.com — aggressive bot-detection breaks unauthenticated checks (2026-04)
# ^https?://(www\.)?(twitter|x)\.com/

# unece.org — 403 to GitHub Actions egress; pages verified live in browser (2026-05)
^https?://unece\.org/
# tesla.com — Cloudflare bot wall returns 403 to CI runners; pages live in browser (2026-05)
^https?://(www\.)?tesla\.com/
# spinningup.openai.com — 403 to CI HEAD requests; site is live (2026-05)
^https?://spinningup\.openai\.com/
# mitpress.mit.edu — 403 to CI; book pages live in browser (2026-05)
^https?://mitpress\.mit\.edu/
# science.org — publisher bot wall returns 403 to CI; DOI links live in browser (2026-05)
^https?://(www\.)?science\.org/
# reddit.com — 403 to unauthenticated CI requests; pages live in browser (2026-05)
^https?://(www\.)?reddit\.com/
# substack.com — 403 to CI HEAD requests across newsletters; live in browser (2026-05)
^https?://[a-z0-9-]+\.substack\.com/
# standardscatalog.ul.com — TLS/network errors from CI runners; site live in browser (2026-05)
^https?://standardscatalog\.ul\.com/
# cds.caltech.edu — intermittent network errors from CI; pages live in browser (2026-05)
^https?://(www\.)?cds\.caltech\.edu/
# stanfordstudentrobotics.org — network errors from CI runners; site live in browser (2026-05)
^https?://stanfordstudentrobotics\.org/
# teach.cs.washington.edu — network errors from CI runners; pages live in browser (2026-05)
^https?://teach\.cs\.washington\.edu/
# robotsandstartups.substack.com — covered by substack.com rule above (2026-05)
# importai.substack.com — covered by substack.com rule above (2026-05)
